cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.THEORY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of graph grammars to program systems of self-assembly and presents a method to simulate asynchronous constant-size-message-passing models of distributed computing with systems of self-assembly. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with the characterization of distributed systems. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses graph rewriting characterization of distributed systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of graph grammars to program systems of self-assembly. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is relevant as the paper presents a generalized version of Soloveichik and Winfree's theorem on local determinism.
